sec.p:
MP may be idiopathic or has been associated with the following conditions:
internal pressure in the pelvis: due to pregnancy, ascites, tumour or obesity;
external pressure: due to tight jeans, rucksacks, tight corsets, wide belts or seat belt injury;
neuropathy: diabetes;
surgery: laparoscopic herniorrhaphy, anterior pelvic procedures, lumbar spine surgery (one series of 110 patients reported an incidence of 12%)6;
pathology of the lumbar nerve root.7
